<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900712-0063</DOCNO><DOCID>900712-0063.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Inmac Corp.:   Company to Reduce Staff   At San Jose, Calif., Plant</HL><DATE>07/12/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   INMC</CO><LP>   Inmac Corp., Santa Clara, Calif., in an effort to stemoperating costs, said it will reduce its work force at thecompany's San Jose, Calif., plant by 73 workers, about 60% ofits work force, effective Aug. 31.   Inmac, which makes a variety of products for use withcomputers,, has more than 1,300 employees in nine countries.</LP><TEXT>   The San Jose plant, the company's only U.S.-basedmanufacturing site, will be kept open and used as thecompany's product testing center, with jobs for about 50 ofits 120 employees, said a company spokesman. Three vicepresident positions have also been eliminated and theirresponsibilities combined into one position.   The reorganization will cost the company about $500,000,or three cents a share, charged to its operating costs forits fiscal fourth-quarter, ending July 28.   The company said it made the move because increasedmanufacturing capabilities at facilities in East Kilbridle,Scotland, and Tijuana, Mexico, along with outside vendors canadequately supply the company production needs.</TEXT></DOC>